72
00:02:51,176 --> 00:02:53,811
President Seibert, I don't
know why you're yelling.

73
00:02:53,813 --> 00:02:56,180
You're the one who made me
go on the radio.

74
00:02:56,182 --> 00:02:59,017
I was expecting a professional
science interview,

75
00:02:59,019 --> 00:03:02,837
not an attack
by some morning zoo shock jock.

76
00:03:04,306 --> 00:03:06,240
Well, if the university
needs money so badly,

77
00:03:06,242 --> 00:03:09,027
perhaps you should start
a swear jar.

78
00:03:10,329 --> 00:03:13,364
Whoa! That one's worth a dollar.

79
00:03:14,666 --> 00:03:16,034
I know you don't like it,

80
00:03:16,036 --> 00:03:17,368
but every time
you do an interview,

81
00:03:17,370 --> 00:03:19,403
it raises the profile
of the university.

82
00:03:19,405 --> 00:03:21,072
That translates to funding.

83
00:03:21,074 --> 00:03:22,090
Yeah, well, I'm not just

84
00:03:22,092 --> 00:03:25,910
some trained monkey
dancing for coins.

85
00:03:25,912 --> 00:03:27,011
Of course you're not.

86
00:03:27,013 --> 00:03:29,047
People love trained monkeys.

87
00:03:31,266 --> 00:03:32,300
How can you not be happy?

88
00:03:32,302 --> 00:03:34,018
You're tall, thin and famous.

89
00:03:34,020 --> 00:03:37,138
Oh, my God,
I'm jealous of Sheldon.

90
00:03:38,390 --> 00:03:39,974
Look, you're gonna be doing
this stuff for a while.

91
00:03:39,976 --> 00:03:42,360
You're just gonna have to find
a way to get used to it.

92
00:03:42,362 --> 00:03:44,261
But none of you know
what this is like.

93
00:03:44,263 --> 00:03:47,431
Being celebrated for something
you wish you never did.

94
00:03:47,433 --> 00:03:50,651
Mmm... you clearly haven't been
with me at Mardi Gras.

95
00:03:54,123 --> 00:03:56,290
Want to pause the video game
and help me clean up?

96
00:03:56,292 --> 00:03:57,458
I am cleaning up.

97
00:03:57,460 --> 00:03:59,877
Look at the mess the Joker made
of Gotham City.

98
00:04:01,080 --> 00:04:03,915
Come on, it's your friend
who's coming to stay here.

99
00:04:03,917 --> 00:04:05,299
Raj grew up in India.

100
00:04:05,301 --> 00:04:07,635
Trust me, he's seen worse.

101
00:04:08,303 --> 00:04:09,453
Howie.

102
00:04:09,455 --> 00:04:10,638
I promise I'll help out

103
00:04:10,640 --> 00:04:11,672
the rest of the week.

104
00:04:11,674 --> 00:04:12,807
The rest of the week?

105
00:04:12,809 --> 00:04:14,625
You said it was just gonna be
a night or two.

106
00:04:14,627 --> 00:04:15,676
Yeah, but if I told you a week,

107
00:04:15,678 --> 00:04:16,594
would you have said yes?

108
00:04:16,596 --> 00:04:20,348
No!
Then you left me no choice.

109
00:04:20,350 --> 00:04:24,018
I love Raj, but that's
a long time for a house guest.

110
00:04:24,020 --> 00:04:25,686
I know, but they're
tenting his building.

111
00:04:25,688 --> 00:04:28,072
He can't find a hotel
he likes that allows dogs.

112
00:04:28,074 --> 00:04:29,640
He's bringing Cinnamon?

113
00:04:29,642 --> 00:04:30,641
For a whole week!

114
00:04:30,643 --> 00:04:32,660
The nerve of some people.

115
00:04:35,197 --> 00:04:39,117
Here comes
the Embarrassment Express.

116
00:04:39,985 --> 00:04:42,587
With stops at Fraudville...

117
00:04:42,589 --> 00:04:45,089
WonderBlunderberg...

118
00:04:45,091 --> 00:04:48,042
and Kansas City.

119
00:04:48,044 --> 00:04:49,310
Because it's a hub.

120
00:04:51,815 --> 00:04:53,281
Sheldon, can I come in?

121
00:04:53,283 --> 00:04:54,932
Do you have cookies?
No.

122
00:04:54,934 --> 00:04:56,884
Good. I don't deserve cookies.
Come in.

123
00:04:58,520 --> 00:05:00,171
Wil...?

124
00:05:00,173 --> 00:05:01,105
Hey, Sheldon.

125
00:05:01,107 --> 00:05:02,023
It's been a while.

126
00:05:02,025 --> 00:05:03,524
Why are you here?

127
00:05:03,526 --> 00:05:04,559
Amy said you were
having a rough time,

128
00:05:04,561 --> 00:05:06,144
and I thought maybe
we could talk.

129
00:05:06,146 --> 00:05:07,011
Is that okay?

130
00:05:07,013 --> 00:05:08,646
Certainly.

131
00:05:08,648 --> 00:05:09,680
Although...

132
00:05:09,682 --> 00:05:11,232
right now,
I'm having a rough time

133
00:05:11,234 --> 00:05:12,900
because there's
three people in my room,

134
00:05:12,902 --> 00:05:15,920
and it's starting to feel
like a discotheque.

135
00:05:17,372 --> 00:05:19,574
Sheldon, you said you were
unhappy getting attention

136
00:05:19,576 --> 00:05:21,859
for something you wished
you never did.

137
00:05:21,861 --> 00:05:23,694
Yeah, I know a little
something about that.

138
00:05:23,696 --> 00:05:25,746
Oh, nonsense, Wil.

139
00:05:25,748 --> 00:05:29,300
Your endless tweets are
not that bad.

140
00:05:29,302 --> 00:05:31,719
I remember why
it's been a while.

141
00:05:31,721 --> 00:05:34,172
Sheldon, I was actually talking

142
00:05:34,174 --> 00:05:35,873
about when I was a kid
on <i>Star Trek.</i>

143
00:05:35,875 --> 00:05:38,392
How could you not
like getting attention

144
00:05:38,394 --> 00:05:39,877
for playing Wesley Crusher?

145
00:05:39,879 --> 00:05:41,996
You were wonderful.

146
00:05:41,998 --> 00:05:44,732
A know-it-all boy genius
with an eidetic memory.

147
00:05:44,734 --> 00:05:47,568
Who couldn't relate to that?

148
00:05:48,437 --> 00:05:50,238
Well, not everybody
felt that way.

149
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:51,989
A lot of people
really hated the character,

150
00:05:51,991 --> 00:05:54,242
and some of them
hated me because of it.

151
00:05:54,244 --> 00:05:55,226
I would do interviews,

152
00:05:55,228 --> 00:05:56,894
and people would be mean to me.

153
00:05:56,896 --> 00:05:59,163
That just happened to me.

154
00:05:59,165 --> 00:06:00,915
Next time you're stuck
for a tweet,

155
00:06:00,917 --> 00:06:04,202
feel free to say
what a jerk Ira Flatow is.

156
00:06:04,204 --> 00:06:07,288
Sheldon, the point is
Wil learned to embrace

157
00:06:07,290 --> 00:06:10,574
that part of his life and moved
on to bigger and better things.

158
00:06:10,576 --> 00:06:12,076
Yeah, I'm an author now,

159
00:06:12,078 --> 00:06:13,628
I do public speaking,

160
00:06:13,630 --> 00:06:15,796
and I have my own Web series
about board games.

161
00:06:15,798 --> 00:06:17,181
Uh...

162
00:06:17,183 --> 00:06:19,050
We're trying
to cheer him up, so...

163
00:06:24,056 --> 00:06:26,023
I'm just saying
that there was a time

164
00:06:26,025 --> 00:06:28,526
when I thought I would never get
out of Wesley Crusher's shadow.

165
00:06:28,528 --> 00:06:29,860
But now,

166
00:06:29,862 --> 00:06:32,313
it's just one small part
of a pretty great life,

167
00:06:32,315 --> 00:06:34,431
and it's a part
that I'm happy is there.

168
00:06:34,433 --> 00:06:36,734
I do see what you're saying.

169
00:06:36,736 --> 00:06:38,236
That helps.

170
00:06:38,238 --> 00:06:39,370
Good.

171
00:06:39,372 --> 00:06:40,605
Would you two like to stay

172
00:06:40,607 --> 00:06:41,639
and play trains with me?

173
00:06:41,641 --> 00:06:42,707
Sure.
Okay.

174
00:06:42,709 --> 00:06:43,774
Oh, great!

175
00:06:43,776 --> 00:06:47,111
Now...

176
00:06:47,113 --> 00:06:48,112
I work the controls.

177
00:06:48,114 --> 00:06:49,297
I say "All aboard""

178
00:06:49,299 --> 00:06:52,283
You sit quietly and watch.

179
00:06:52,285 --> 00:06:54,385
Can I blow the whistle?

180
00:06:55,754 --> 00:06:57,755
You should probably go.

181
00:07:05,314 --> 00:07:07,415
You're gonna brush
your teeth on my couch?

182
00:07:07,417 --> 00:07:10,568
No, I'm gonna brush
Cinnamon's teeth.

183
00:07:10,570 --> 00:07:11,686
Why bother?

184
00:07:11,688 --> 00:07:12,820
She spends half the time

185
00:07:12,822 --> 00:07:14,322
licking her butt.

186
00:07:15,274 --> 00:07:16,741
And the other half
licking my face.

187
00:07:16,743 --> 00:07:18,809
That's why I'm brushing
her teeth.

188
00:07:20,645 --> 00:07:22,646
Hey, guys.
Sorry I'm so late.

189
00:07:22,648 --> 00:07:23,647
Did you already have dinner?

190
00:07:23,649 --> 00:07:25,249
No, we were waiting for you.

191
00:07:25,251 --> 00:07:26,500
Aw, that's so sweet.

192
00:07:26,502 --> 00:07:28,753
Yeah. So what do you
feel like making?

193
00:07:30,322 --> 00:07:31,505
Howard, the poor thing

194
00:07:31,507 --> 00:07:32,506
just got home from work.

195
00:07:32,508 --> 00:07:34,658
Let me get you a glass of wine.

196
00:07:34,660 --> 00:07:36,177
I'll cook dinner.

197
00:07:36,179 --> 00:07:38,129
- Oh, Raj, you're our guest.
- Don't be silly.

198
00:07:38,131 --> 00:07:40,164
Sit. You look
like you've had a long day.

199
00:07:40,166 --> 00:07:43,150
No, she always
looks like that.

200
00:07:45,554 --> 00:07:48,939
Because she married an idiot.

201
00:07:49,691 --> 00:07:51,592
Thank you, Raj.

202
00:07:51,594 --> 00:07:52,810
Please, this is

203
00:07:52,812 --> 00:07:54,528
my way of thanking you

204
00:07:54,530 --> 00:07:56,364
for letting me stay here.

205
00:07:56,366 --> 00:07:59,317
Now, tell us all about your day.

206
00:07:59,319 --> 00:08:01,319
Okay, um, well, first,

207
00:08:01,321 --> 00:08:03,287
I was late to a meeting
'cause I was stuck in traffic.

208
00:08:03,289 --> 00:08:06,290
Well, I keep telling you to put
that traffic app on your phone.

209
00:08:06,292 --> 00:08:08,192
Hey, when you got home today
complaining that you felt sick

210
00:08:08,194 --> 00:08:09,526
from eating
too many jelly beans,

211
00:08:09,528 --> 00:08:10,661
did I tell you how to fix it?

212
00:08:10,663 --> 00:08:11,862
No.

213
00:08:13,548 --> 00:08:17,534
I said, "Aw, that must hurt,"
and I rubbed your belly.

214
00:08:20,872 --> 00:08:23,090
I thought of you
the whole time.

215
00:08:26,228 --> 00:08:28,179
All I'm saying is there's
a time to just listen.

216
00:08:28,181 --> 00:08:29,513
Thank you.

217
00:08:29,515 --> 00:08:30,598
There's also a time to stop

218
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:31,682
eating too many jelly beans.

219
00:08:31,684 --> 00:08:33,851
And it's when you're ten.

220
00:08:36,655 --> 00:08:38,255
Hello, President Siebert.

221
00:08:38,257 --> 00:08:39,774
Thank you for taking my call.

222
00:08:39,776 --> 00:08:42,576
I just wanted you to know
that you can now expect

223
00:08:42,578 --> 00:08:46,414
enthusiastic participation
from me regarding my discovery.

224
00:08:46,416 --> 00:08:47,698
Oh, no, no, no, no.

225
00:08:47,700 --> 00:08:48,999
No need to thank me.

226
00:08:49,001 --> 00:08:51,786
Thank my friend, Wil Wheaton.

227
00:08:51,788 --> 00:08:55,005
For your information,
I have nine friends, hmm?

228
00:08:56,208 --> 00:08:59,410
Ten if we include you.

229
00:08:59,412 --> 00:09:01,595
Nine it is.

230
00:09:04,182 --> 00:09:06,183
Ah, it's ten.

231
00:09:06,185 --> 00:09:08,018
I'll count Wolowitz.

232
00:09:08,920 --> 00:09:10,771
Hello, friend Leonard.

233
00:09:10,773 --> 00:09:12,056
Hey, you're in a good mood.

234
00:09:12,058 --> 00:09:14,024
I'm in a great mood.

235
00:09:14,026 --> 00:09:15,893
Well, you're about to be
in an even better one.

236
00:09:15,895 --> 00:09:17,261
I didn't want
to say anything

237
00:09:17,263 --> 00:09:18,646
until I knew for sure, but...

238
00:09:18,648 --> 00:09:21,365
I've been re-running the tests
on your element in my lab

239
00:09:21,367 --> 00:09:22,900
and I disproved it.

240
00:09:22,902 --> 00:09:24,702
Your element does not exist!

241
00:09:25,737 --> 00:09:27,471
Yeah, but what about
the Chinese research team?

242
00:09:27,473 --> 00:09:28,572
They found it.

243
00:09:28,574 --> 00:09:29,957
Yeah, it turns out someone added

244
00:09:29,959 --> 00:09:32,443
simulated signals
to the data files.

245
00:09:32,445 --> 00:09:34,128
They faked the results.

246
00:09:34,130 --> 00:09:35,129
Really?

247
00:09:35,131 --> 00:09:36,864
Yes! Do you know
what that means?

248
00:09:36,866 --> 00:09:39,884
That means all of this attention
that you hate goes away.

249
00:09:39,886 --> 00:09:41,118
So no more interviews?

250
00:09:41,120 --> 00:09:42,119
No, it's all over.

251
00:09:42,121 --> 00:09:43,220
I can't believe it.

252
00:09:43,222 --> 00:09:44,121
Well, you're welcome.

253
00:09:44,123 --> 00:09:45,122
You robbed me

254
00:09:45,124 --> 00:09:47,057
of my greatest achievement!

255
00:09:48,043 --> 00:09:49,009
What?!

256
00:09:49,011 --> 00:09:51,812
I'm back down
to nine friends!

257
00:09:51,814 --> 00:09:55,232
Make it eight--
I'm sick of Wolowitz, too!

258
00:09:55,234 --> 00:09:57,735
I-I don't understand.

259
00:09:57,737 --> 00:09:59,353
All you've done
since you discovered

